title: "AgentLoom: Executable Governance Framework for Builder Agents"
abstract: >
  AgentLoom v3 is a runnable framework for knowledge-graph-grounded agent governance:
  propose-review-accept protocol, eight Tier-A executable validators, JSON-schema KG
  integrity checks, and a read-only human review dashboard. Builder and domain roles
  share one governance model; domain knowledge accumulates through audited proposals
  rather than ad-hoc prompt edits. Dual-helix architecture (learning + governance)
  positions the framework for trustworthy agentic AI in production settings.
  Patterns were generalized from production research data lifecycle management at an
  academic library (EnviStor); public releases are framework-only and domain-neutral.
